{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The review input is scoped to the lines that changed, not the full content of each modified file.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS is yes: a unit test of a single formatter can pass while real wiring still feeds full files. REAL-INFRA is not required; this can be reproduced with local diff fixtures. MOCK-HIDE risk is in module boundaries (diff extraction -> prompt assembly), so Integration is the minimum real failure boundary.","test_description":"Run the review-input builder against a realistic unified diff fixture with multiple files and unchanged regions. Assert the final model input includes only added/modified hunks and excludes untouched file content. Use real local modules wired together (diff parser + scoping + prompt builder), no network.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.24,"Integration":0.66,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Inline comments are attached to the correct positions in the diff view on the pull request.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA is yes: correctness depends on GitHub PR diff-position semantics and API behavior. MOCK-HIDE is high: mocked APIs often accept invalid position mappings that GitHub rejects or anchors differently. Therefore minimum is System.","test_description":"Against a real test PR on GitHub, post inline comments using the automation’s computed anchors (path/line/side or position). Verify via fetched PR review comments that each comment appears on the intended changed line in the diff view and is not marked outdated immediately.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.16,"System":0.79,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The agent identifies at least one real defect in a pull request that contains a known introduced bug.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP is yes: this checks defect-finding quality, not just wiring. Outcomes can vary across runs/prompts/models. Even with stable infra, correctness depends on real model judgment. Minimum is Agentic.","test_description":"Use a seeded test PR containing a known bug (e.g., swallowed exception or off-by-one). Run the real review model call and assert at least one inline finding correctly targets the buggy change. Repeat across N runs (or fixed evaluation set) and enforce a pass threshold to handle model variance.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.06}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Every finding listed in the top-level summary corresponds to an inline comment that was also posted — no findings appear in the summary without a matching inline comment.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"MOCK-HIDE is meaningful: local mocks may report inline posts as successful while real API calls can fail/partial-fail, causing summary drift. The behavior is about what was actually posted on the PR, so real external state is part of the boundary. Minimum is System.","test_description":"Run automation on a real PR, then fetch both top-level summary comment and inline review comments from GitHub. Parse finding identifiers (or normalized tuples: file+line+message hash) and assert summary set is a subset of successfully posted inline comments, with no extra summary-only finding.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.04,"Integration":0.34,"System":0.52,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full sequence — reading the diff, posting inline comments, posting the summary comment — completes correctly for a real pull request without manual intervention.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is an end-to-end agent pipeline spanning multiple stages and dependencies, including agentic defect generation plus external PR mutations. MULTI-STEP/full pipeline applies, so Workflow is the minimum boundary.","test_description":"Execute the automation as a black-box run on a real GitHub test PR from trigger to completion. Verify all stages succeed in order: diff read, at least expected inline comment attempts, summary posted, and final status reported without human edits/retries. Validate artifacts on GitHub after run.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.02,"System":0.18,"Agentic":0.24,"Workflow":0.56}}]}
